60.4	Enola_Gay	Enola Gay	Enola Gay is a Boeing B-29 Superfortress bomber, named after Enola Gay Tibbets, mother of the pilot, then-Colonel (later Brigadier General) Paul Tibbets. On 6 August 1945, during the final stages of World War II, it became the first aircraft to drop an atomic bomb as a weapon of war. The bomb, code-named "Little Boy", was targeted at the city of Hiroshima, Japan, and caused extensive destruction.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Tibbets-wave.jpg/210px-Tibbets-wave.jpg
